race.comment: BIG PAPA (12) justified the short price on debut ($1.35 fav), when an effortless on-pace winner over 1100m at Bathurst. Looks to be airborne after the two impressive trial wins and resumes in a winnable contest. GAMBLER (4) finally got off the mark at start five when ploughing through the heavy (8) going for a determined win over 1000m at Kembla Grange. Impressed in two trials and looks set for a solid campaign. CHARLEROI (1) Dundeel gelding with upside who will find this short of his best first-up. Lugging-bit goes on and look for him charging late with the two good trials. OCTA DE LAGO (5) resumes for her second campaign. Had the two soft trials and look for him late.
